How to use?


Just execute "./client.sh" and "./server.sh" in separate terminals.
The virtual machines will start and you can play around with them.


The IP-Addresses of each virtual machine are:
client: eth0 - 10.1.1.2 , eth1 - 10.1.2.2
server: eth0 - 10.2.1.2

Login/Password of both machines is root/root

Both virtual machines have ssh/scp, iperf, lighttpd installed.
Public/Private keys for ssh-authentication are already setup.

The network interfaces are properly configured upon the boot by /etc/network/interfaces

